This document is a copy of an official architectural drawing for Boys & Girls High School in Brooklyn, New York. It includes three elevation views—Part North, Part South, and West—with total floor area measurements indicated on each plan. The building's design incorporates modern materials such as wood framing with rubber gaskets and stainless steel bracing, metal concrete paneling or plastic shell structures, low-e coating windows to enhance energy efficiency, new HVAC systems including refrigerated air conditioning units and heat pumps, and scheduled completion dates set for April 2024. All drawings are reviewed and approved before construction begins under strict city code enforcement guidelines. This project has been designed using advanced engineering techniques ensuring structural integrity while maintaining high performance standards across multiple dimensions.
